The scandal bank of Lake Zurich
The most adventurous bank in Europe is not in Italy or France, but in Switzerland.
UBS almost went bankrupt during the financial crisis and has been slipping from one crisis to the next ever since.
Now I want a German to fix it.
I'm sure Axel Weber didn't think of it that way.
After his spectacular departure from the Bundesbank, it was announced in July that he would take up an almost equally spectacular new job in 2013: Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Swiss major bank UBS - an unexpected and lucrative career move.
Axel Weber was happy in public, praised Switzerland for its beauty and UBS for its newfound solidity and made friendly remarks about the future colleagues.
"UBS has made the turnaround".
"I look forward to working with Kaspar Villiger and Oswald Grübel".
But by September it was clear that things would be very different.
A UBS dealer in London had bypassed all the bank's security systems and embezzled about 1.7 billion euros.
UBS CEO Oswald Grübel, a banker famous not only in Switzerland, had to leave.
The chairman of the board of directors of UBS has also been considered a victim since then - and everyone is asking: when will Axel Weber finally come?
