The idea of becoming the custodian of the world's great fortunes, not taking too great risks, but ensuring the safety of money - should the world collapse even beyond the Alpine republic - had long ago been the idea of the Swiss bankers.
The vaults of Swiss banks had become a symbol of unshakable reliability, like Lindt and Sprüngli for particularly fine chocolate.
The headquarters of UBS in Zurich still fits the cliché of the established Swiss private bank - it is only a little bigger.
