Bacio Cortés died a few days ago when the helicopter he was flying crashed, carrying Secretary of State José Francisco Blake Mora and six other officials from the same agency.
At 18:05 the cremated remains of Bacio Cortés, a citizen of Saltillo, arrived to be handed over to members of the Mexican Air Force, led by Major Jaime Martinez, by the funeral company in the front square of the barracks, where his family members, including his daughter Amanda and his wife Cristina, his mother, siblings and other relatives, students and teachers were already waiting for him.
